<node CREATED="1422389962239" ID="ID_1140960141" MODIFIED="1422805546664" TEXT="English">
<node CREATED="1422440757577" ID="ID_231680616" MODIFIED="1422440760055" TEXT="derivative"/>
<node CREATED="1422389970646" ID="ID_61677321" MODIFIED="1422390794420">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      In finance, <b>a derivative is a contract that derives its value from the performance of an underlying entity</b>. This underlying entity can be an asset, index, or interest rate, and is often called the &quot;underlying&quot;.[1][2] Derivatives can be used for a number of purposes - including insuring against price movements (hedging), increasing exposure to price movements for speculation or getting access to otherwise hard to trade assets or markets
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
